HEADWORD: Eudiometry
<hw>Eu`di*om"e*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>eudiom⟦eacute⟧trie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The art or
process of determining the constituents of a gaseous mixture by means of
the eudiometer, or for ascertaining the purity of the air or the amount
of oxygen in it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

